Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with torch symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 80, 21. Name Rodippos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0400.19.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0763)
